# CultBot cron example (Option A).
#
# Install:  crontab -e   (then paste one of the lines below)
# Inspect:  crontab -l
#
# Cron uses the machine's LOCAL time. Confirm the zone first:
#   timedatectl                                  # check "Time zone"
#   sudo timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Kolkata   # set it if needed
#
# Fields:  minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week   command
#
# Edit two things before pasting:
#   1. The time (here 22:01 = 10:01 PM) to a minute after your window opens.
#   2. The path /home/pi/CultBot to your actual checkout.

# Book daily at 22:01 local time, appending output to a log file.
1 22 * * * cd /home/pi/CultBot && /usr/bin/env node index.js book >> /home/pi/CultBot/cultbot.log 2>&1

# If node is not on cron's PATH (e.g. installed via nvm), use the absolute path
# from `which node`:
# 1 22 * * * cd /home/pi/CultBot && /home/pi/.nvm/versions/node/v22.0.0/bin/node index.js book >> /home/pi/CultBot/cultbot.log 2>&1

# The redirected log grows forever. Rotate it with the ready-made snippet in
# deploy/cultbot.logrotate.
